<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>

    <head>
        <title>My shaandaar todolist</title>
        <style>
            a {
                text-decoration: none;
                color: black;
            }

        </style>
    </head>

    <body>
        <h1>Hello there!!
        
        Here's a general to-do list for a DevOps career roadmap:

Learn the fundamentals of programming: If you haven't already, start learning at least one programming language. You should be able to write basic scripts, understand programming concepts and structures, and be comfortable working with data.

Gain expertise in at least one scripting language: DevOps professionals typically use scripting languages such as Python, Bash, Ruby, and PowerShell. Pick one and become proficient with it.

Learn about operating systems: You should have a good understanding of how operating systems work, including how they manage memory, handle files, and interact with hardware.

Get comfortable with the command line: You should be able to navigate and work effectively with command-line interfaces.

Learn about source control: Learn Git or other source control tools like SVN to manage code effectively.

Gain knowledge of containerization technologies: Containerization has become a crucial part of modern DevOps practice, so it's essential to gain experience with containerization technologies like Docker.

Learn about infrastructure as code: Infrastructure as code (IaC) allows you to automate the creation, deployment, and management of infrastructure. Gain knowledge of tools like Terraform, CloudFormation.

Familiarize yourself with cloud platforms: It's important to understand how cloud platforms such as AWS, Azure, and GCP work, how to deploy applications on them and how to monitor them.

Learn about CI/CD tools: Continuous integration/continuous deployment (CI/CD) is an essential part of DevOps practice. Familiarize yourself with tools like Jenkins, Travis CI, CircleCI.

Gain experience in monitoring and logging: Monitoring and logging are crucial for maintaining the health of your infrastructure. Learn about tools like Prometheus, Grafana, and ELK stack.

Develop soft skills: DevOps involves working closely with multiple teams. To be successful, you must have excellent communication skills and be comfortable working in a fast-paced environment.

Stay updated with the latest trends: DevOps is a rapidly evolving field, and staying updated with the latest trends and technologies is essential. Attend conferences, read blogs and participate in online communities.

Remember, this list is just a starting point. DevOps is a broad field, and you will need to specialize in a specific area to advance your career. Good luck!</h1>
        <ul>
            <% todolist.forEach(function(todo, index) { %>
            <li>
                <a href="/todo/delete/<%= index %>">✘</a>
                <a href="/todo/<%= index %>">✎</a>
                <%- todo %>
            </li>
            <% }); %>
        </ul>

        <form action="/todo/add/" method="post">
            <p>
                <label for="newtodo">What shoud I do?</label>
                <input type="text" name="newtodo" id="newtodo" autofocus />
                <input type="submit" value="Add" />
            </p>
        </form>
    </body>

</html>
